cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of rare subclasses in neural network classifiers, which is a common issue in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes an approach for detecting and mitigating these rare subclasses, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as rare subclasses can also lead to unwanted bias in decision-making systems. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
